@parties
go-to: menu

**CDU/CSU** - *Christlich Demokratische Union Deutschlands* (Christian Democratic Party of Germany - This is us, we are the the major party of the centre-right in German politics and have been in charge for most of post-war german history.

**SPD** - *Sozialdemokratische Partei Deutschlands (Social Democratic Party of Germany) - Our former rival party. They are a centre-left social democratic party. They are the oldest party in German history, having been formed in the German Empire era.

Current relations: [+ sdp_relation : relationships +]

# TODO: replace this with the german state party after 1930
**Greens** - *Bündnis 90/Die Grünen* (Alliance 90/The Greens) - a center-left green liberal party. The Greens have been the most hawkish and militaristic out of any other party, despite their liberal outlook.

Current relations: [+ ddp_relation : relationships +]

**FDP** - *Freie Demokratische Partei* (Free Democratic Party) - a market-liberal party. We have formed many coalitions with them over the years.

Current relations: [+ dvp_relation : relationships +]

**AfD** - *Deutschnationale Volkspartei* (German National People's Party) - a right-wing nationalist-conservative party, with authoritarian, neo-nazi, and racist elements. It is a offshoot from our party, and has been hostile to us.

Current relations: [+ dnvp_relation : relationships +]

**Die Linke** - *Die Linke* (The Left) - a radical left-wing party that had gained the favour in eastern Germany, historically under a communist dictatorship. Many of them abandoned soviet ideals and instead work towards parlaimentarianism which gave them a wider audience.

Current relations: [+ kpd_relation : relationships +]

